{
  "doc_id": "21678",
  "text": "Serum levels for insulin increased with age in Htr1b KO mice, suggesting that the lower levels in young KO mice were not due to primary deficits in hormone production. The direction of changes also suggests that hormonal levels are not mediating the age-related phenotype of Htr1b KO mice for two reasons. First, increased levels above normal, rather than lower insulin levels, are associated with deleterious effects of aging. [CITATION_1] Second, earlier studies in model organisms, [CITATION_2] including mice, 51 predict a protective effect of decreased IGF-1 levels against aging.",
